### Probation Tracker MCP — debug HTTP tests
### Use with the VS Code "REST Client" (humao.rest-client) extension.
### Press the "Send Request" link above each request.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Variables
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
@tunnelMcp     = https://f0r8gwwh-3001.uks1.devtunnels.ms/mcp
@localMcp      = http://localhost:3001/mcp
@tenantId      = 0c2614e6-a76a-433c-80fd-88ac91e67b9d

# App registration (calendar plugin uses SSO via TDP; secret only needed for OBO server-side, not here)
@clientId      = 54881055-411d-41b2-8f25-f1312a1abfe6

# Common headers (MCP Streamable HTTP)
@accept        = application/json, text/event-stream

# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 1 — Local probation MCP server (no auth)
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 1.1 Health probe (root)
GET http://localhost:3001/

### 1.2 initialize (REQUIRED first call per MCP spec)
# @name probLocalInit
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "initialize",
  "params": {
    "protocolVersion": "2025-06-18",
    "capabilities": {},
    "clientInfo": { "name": "rest-client", "version": "0.0.1" }
  }
}

### 1.3 tools/list
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 2, "method": "tools/list" }

### 1.4 resources/list (should return 3 ui://probation/*.html resources)
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 3, "method": "resources/list" }

### 1.5 tools/call → show-probation-dashboard (no filters)
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 4, "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "show-probation-dashboard",
    "arguments": {}
  }
}

### 1.6 tools/call → show-probationer-detail by name
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 5, "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "show-probationer-detail",
    "arguments": { "name": "Sarah" }
  }
}

### 1.7 tools/call → show-probation-reports
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 6, "method": "tools/call",
  "params": { "name": "show-probation-reports", "arguments": {} }
}

### 1.8 Read a UI resource
POST {{localMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 7, "method": "resources/read",
  "params": { "uri": "ui://probation/dashboard.html" }
}

# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 2 — Same probation MCP through the dev tunnel
# (what M365 Copilot actually hits)
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

### 2.1 initialize through tunnel
POST {{tunnelMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 1, "method": "initialize",
  "params": {
    "protocolVersion": "2025-06-18",
    "capabilities": {},
    "clientInfo": { "name": "rest-client", "version": "0.0.1" }
  }
}

### 2.2 tools/list through tunnel
POST {{tunnelMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json

{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 2, "method": "tools/list" }

# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# SECTION 3 — Work IQ Calendar MCP (1P Microsoft service, requires SSO)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# The plugin URL Copilot calls. Auth uses Microsoft Entra SSO — Work IQ
# needs a DELEGATED user token (it acts as the signed-in user), so we use
# the OAuth 2.0 device code flow. Client credentials would NOT work since
# the calendar is per-user.
#
# Flow:
#   1. "Send Request" on `### 3.0 Request a device code`.
#   2. Open the verification_uri shown in the response (https://microsoft.com/devicelogin)
#      and enter the user_code.
#   3. After signing in, "Send Request" on `### 3.0b Poll for the token`
#      (re-send if it returns "authorization_pending").
#   4. Fire 3.1, 3.2, 3.3 etc. — they reference {{token.response.body.access_token}}.
#
# Alternative — paste a token from `az account get-access-token`:
#   az login --tenant 0c2614e6-a76a-433c-80fd-88ac91e67b9d
#   az account get-access-token --resource "https://agent365.svc.cloud.microsoft" --query accessToken -o tsv
#   Replace @workiqToken below with the literal eyJ... value.
# ═════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

@workiqMcp     = https://agent365.svc.cloud.microsoft/agents/tenants/{{tenantId}}/servers/mcp_CalendarTools
@workiqResource = https://agent365.svc.cloud.microsoft
@workiqScope   = {{workiqResource}}/.default

### 3.0-pre OAuth protected resource metadata (no auth required)
# Tells MCP clients which Entra resource/scopes to request a token for.
# Copilot uses this to discover auth automatically — so the plugin manifest
# should NOT need to declare an `auth` block for first-party MCPs.
GET {{workiqMcp}}/.well-known/oauth-protected-resource
Accept: application/json

### 3.0 Request a device code (delegated user flow)
# @name devicecode
POST https://login.microsoftonline.com/{{tenantId}}/oauth2/v2.0/devicecode
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

client_id={{clientId}}
&scope={{workiqScope}} offline_access

### 3.0b Poll for the token (run after signing in at the verification_uri)
# @name token
POST https://login.microsoftonline.com/{{tenantId}}/oauth2/v2.0/token
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

grant_type=urn:ietf:params:oauth:grant-type:device_code
&client_id={{clientId}}
&device_code={{devicecode.response.body.device_code}}

### Reference the token captured above. To paste an az-CLI token instead,
### replace this line with `@workiqToken = ey...`.
@workiqToken   = {{token.response.body.access_token}}

### 3.1 initialize (REQUIRED first call)
# @name workiqInit
POST {{workiqMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{workiqToken}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0",
  "id": 1,
  "method": "initialize",
  "params": {
    "protocolVersion": "2025-06-18",
    "capabilities": {},
    "clientInfo": { "name": "rest-client", "version": "0.0.1" }
  }
}

### 3.2 tools/list — should return mcp_CalendarTools_graph_* tools
POST {{workiqMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{workiqToken}}

{ "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 2, "method": "tools/list" }

### 3.3 tools/call → mcp_CalendarTools_graph_listEvents (top 10)
POST {{workiqMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{workiqToken}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 3, "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "mcp_CalendarTools_graph_listEvents",
    "arguments": { "top": 10 }
  }
}

### 3.4 tools/call → mcp_CalendarTools_graph_findMeetingTimes (1-hour slot)
POST {{workiqMcp}}
Accept: {{accept}}
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer {{workiqToken}}

{
  "jsonrpc": "2.0", "id": 4, "method": "tools/call",
  "params": {
    "name": "mcp_CalendarTools_graph_findMeetingTimes",
    "arguments": { "meetingDuration": "PT1H", "maxCandidates": 3 }
  }
}

